It looks this change will port the datastore selection logic into oslo.vmware. Currently these logics lies in ds_util.py of nova. I am wondering if these datastore related logics should belong to upper layer logic(Nova). As within nova part, this will give much flexibility to alter the datastore logic, for example if want to add a more interested property of the datastore such as "NFS" returned for get_datastore. 

Also _get_host_ref for the Host case, would hardcode to get the first host belong to the cluster. Cases like these might be changed somehow in the future. Putting them in oslo package does not seem to be a good idea. Or at least oslo.vmware need to extended the method to allow callers to define the expected results and properties.'}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-08-25 11:41:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

(3 comments)

The datastore selection is a two step process:
1. filter the available datastores based on some criteria (image type, configured regex, configured storage policy, etc.)
2. select the most preferable datastore based on some other criteria (largest free space, number of hosts connected, etc.)

We need pluggable mechanism for both steps, not only for the second one. The other requirement is that we need to be able to change those in runtime, i.e. they should be dynamic. For example stream optimized images can be deployed also on 'vSAN' datastores, not only on VMFS and NFS.

I think we can address those requirements with the current design and I'll be happy to review again."}, {'account_id': 7148, 'date': '2014-08-26 08:39:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

Dims, I am thinking that all the component project such as nova with vmware functionality would migrate to adopt the oslo.vmware package. 

I am not opposed to have the ds_util logics moved to oslo.vmware under that it's can make it more easily be extended or configured by Nova(such as add the a more property to return). 

And for the datastore selection policy specifically, I think there might be some other policies would require more arguments than only datastores. For example, sometimes it would be valuable to pick up a datastore within minimum binded Host Or VMs with priorities. Anyway, this is a good to get start."}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-08-26 17:12:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 19:

@Radoslav, great comments, will rework.

@ZhuZhu, agree to your comments. please do keep an eye on this and suggest changes that will work for everyone.'}, {'account_id': 10327, 'date': '2014-08-29 08:38:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 19: Code-Review-1

'}, {'created': '2014-08-18 19:43:14.000000000', 'message': "VMWare: Support for pluggable Datastore selection

First step was to port get_datastore and get_available_datastores and
make it work with the oslo.vmware infrastructure (sessions, exceptions etc).
Next step was to add a base class DataStoreSelectionPolicy with two concrete
implementations namely LargestDataSelectionPolicy (existing use case) and
RandomDataSelectionPolicy (from review 106694). We use stevedore, so anyone
can define their own selection policies implementation, add it to setup.cfg
and use it. Note that we are not adding a CONF option here, but that is
needed to be done in projects like Nova/Cinder etc. the policy is defaulted
to 'largest' which is the existing functionality.

Change-Id: I6d1f8cf703a3ebe96f52a934065a301dc1576e66

commit_message:
VMWare: Support for pluggable Datastore selection

First step was to port get_datastore and get_available_datastores and
make it work with the oslo.vmware infrastructure (sessions, exceptions etc).
Next step was to add a base class DataStoreSelectionPolicy with two concrete
implementations namely LargestDataSelectionPolicy (existing use case) and
RandomDataSelectionPolicy (from review 106694). We use stevedore, so anyone
can define their own selection policies implementation, add it to setup.cfg
and use it. Note that we are not adding a CONF option here, but that is
needed to be done in projects like Nova/Cinder etc. the policy is defaulted
to 'largest' which is the existing functionality.  This includes the change
to skip datastores in maintenance mode as well.

Change-Id: I6d1f8cf703a3ebe96f52a934065a301dc1576e66
Closes-Bug: #1340564

commit_message:
Auto generate the API documentation

Once we use the pbr based build to generate files, we prune
the indexes to remove references to code we would like to
hide like the common modules and private modules in conf.py.
We reuse the same excluded_patterns variable that is already
used in Sphinx and filter these modules from autoindex.rst

Change-Id: Iec89570aa90defd0fb21610e99d0ddf565a5b4b0

commit_message:
Fix comments from 111429, rev 22

This cleans up our method of getting a flavor from an instance,
as pointed out by dansmith on

also pointed this out in rev 13, in a different way).

commit_message:
Add API documentation to docs build

Once we use the pbr based build to generate files, we prune
the indexes to remove references to code we would like to
hide like the common modules and private modules in conf.py.
We reuse the same excluded_patterns variable that is already
used in Sphinx and filter these modules from autoindex.rst

Change-Id: I4cf8d6fbce070101fe858465ed7572b1d03dca2f

An explicit fsync is usually wrong (and needs copious comments to justify if ever used). 

I don't see how an fsync helps here, only acting as a big hammer to avoid a possible race.

Can we explain why the temp file needs to be written to disk before processing? One thing that comes to mind is if `qemu-img convert` used fiemap to efficiently read the image but didn't sync first. That's due a kernel bug in fiemap IMHO, but qemu-img should avoid that itself if using the fiemap interface rather than pushing it higher.

So in summary we need to classify the problem a lot more before applying fixes with possibly large side effects like this. I.E. what platforms, what qemu-img version, what file system, ..."}, {'account_id': 12710, 'date': '2014-09-09 08:22:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

The issue could be reproduced in the same manner with both qemu-img versions 2.0.0 and and the recently released 2.1.0. The operating system is Ubuntu Server 14.04, the file system hosting the temp file is ext4.'}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-09-09 11:55:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

p-draigbrady, does it help that the fsync is not global, it's just for the specific file?"}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-09-09 12:08:55.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-09-09 12:09:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

It doesn't really help that the fsync is for the file, as depending on file system that can serialize the whole file system. Anyway the main problem I have is I can't see why not is there an explanation as to why this temp file needs to leave the page cache?"}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-09-09 13:18:22.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

commit_message:
Fix for intermittent corruption of base images

We need to fsync the image once we write it to a file
after downloading it from glance.

Closes-Bug: #1350766
Change-Id: I3bc44eb667e8ddc09e0bbe69b011f945b42ea593

commit_message:
Making section id names readable in security guide

In the security guide, the section id names are the chapter name
with a random id number on the end. This is harder to work with and not
really necessary, for example,
case-studies-system-documentation-idp44480. Replacing section id names with
"case-studies-system-documentation-alice-private-cloud".

Changing the ids at the section definitions for case studies throughout.
No references are made to these section ids within security guide and
hence no changes needed there.

Partial-Bug: #1340388

Change-Id: Ibaccd164332239dc9d701a74f5b84c2fd357feb6

commit_message:
Handle invalidate in identity plugins correctly

Returning a True from the invalidate() call means that something has
changed within the plugin and the session should reissue the request and
expect the plugin to authenticate itself.

This means we should only return True if something actually changed,
because re-issuing the request if there was no auth_ref will not change
the outcome.

commit_message:
Update paste pipelines in configuration docs

Currently we use a really old value for an example paste pipeline,
this patch updates the example text to the most recent value.

Change-Id: I447c16a088f5394e1599018c6011da010f8d3e0d

commit_message:
Allow providing an endpoint_override to requests

As much as I'd prefer not to need this functionality there are plenty of
existing clients that we want to have use the adapter that can accept a
bypass argument such that it ignores the service catalog and uses that
URL for all requests.

We therefore need to be able to support similar functionality in our
adapter.

Change-Id: I206705241ff9b84967d0d9c089b4795bcc26b65e

commit_message:
Standardize usage of client arguments (networking-guide)

Like documented at https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions#Client_arguments:_.22--option_ARGUMENT.22
we prefer to use '--option ARGUMENT'.

Change-Id: I0481252ff433a7edb52a8670a07a524cc7bd0b8e

commit_message:
Add support for ipv6 nameservers

Update interfaces.template to support ipv6 based dns servers. Make
sure we validate the version of the ip addresses before we
fill them in.

Closes-Bug: #1355777

Change-Id: I7229656bfa5ff5a29c63befc3b9ce91c46e04723

commit_message:
Fix lost content escaping for html safety

During generator refactoring to enable the swift backend, we
incorrectly set a state flag which meant we *never* escaped < > any
more. Apparently it took a while for people to notice.

The fix is to actually correctly set the flag in the _discover_html
function. A unit test is added to ensure that we don't break this
again in the future.

Change-Id: Ifa9d34c45047a257a392c729aaf792f17d8ff453
Closes-Bug: #1367021

commit_message:
Remove XML from api doc samples

v1 API doc samples include XML:
  http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ironic/webapi/v1.html
However, the Ironic API does not support XML.

This removes the XML documentation from the generated docs.

Change-Id: I0588709190eafa52a252d19a163dc42c36f2e061
Closes-Bug: #1311268

commit_message:
ignore .idea folder in ceilometer

If we use JetBrains PyCharm as python develop tool, JetBrains PyCharm
would automatically generate its config folder name .idea in the root
dir of your python code.
Many Code projects, such as nova and cinder, have ignore .idea folder.
Project ceilometer should also ignore .idea folder.

Closes-Bug: #1362489
Change-Id: I1b6ce2101cdf752cbe5719b9488bc3e3ab24a9a4

commit_message:
Fixes bug with put item predefined attributes

Fixes bug that prevents setting to 'null' item
predefined attributes, that are not mentioned
in put request.

Closes-bug: #1348336
Change-Id: I5ad0db7ea81224c2a6f42a4f792f1dbf28f85c90

[{'created': '2014-08-15 01:18:09.000000000', 'message': 'To optimize the detach_volume code

To optimize the detach_volume code. The db_volume_detached can return the
Volume_info, so we need not get volume_info from DB after call
db_volume_detached.

Change-Id: I217252b44bf77420ac909b07612f707a1ab4e83a
Closes-Bug: #1357147
'}]
commit_message:
To optimize the detach_volume code

To optimize the detach_volume code. The db_volume_detached can return the
Volume_info, so we need not get volume_info from DB after call
db_volume_detached.

Change-Id: I217252b44bf77420ac909b07612f707a1ab4e83a
Closes-Bug: #1357147

commit_message:
Changed serial console setup

The previous method only configured serial console for Ubuntu or
Fedora, I noticed this wasn't working when I built RedHat 7.
After reading about how grub-mkconfig works, I realized that we
shouldn't be using sed to modify grub.cfg, and set up the proper
variables in /etc/default/grub

Change-Id: I02b73dc5074cb48a716849cb8a8a9b2f054bea31

commit_message:
Upgrades, copy cobbler files right after container is created

Supervisor start is too slow, puppet run (and cobbler sync)
passes before we copy the data for cobbler.

The solution is to copy all required files right
after container is created.

Change-Id: I6b4b0ab879d31e43a70e5c9e72c83b1de47ddfb2
Related-bug: #1366875

commit_message:
Trigger cobbler_sync after profile creation

Set cobbler_sync to always run every puppet
run just in case. Nailgun cobbler sync should
trigger after profile creation.

Closes-Bug: #1366875

Change-Id: I9107e42374e0013e63a40856af7224e3811b6063

commit_message:
diff_branches: add the project sources in sys.path

Pickle needs to access some classes available during the serialization
in autohelp.py, so add the sources in the python path to make sur that
the deserialization works.

Change-Id: I3295ebd0cf763984b2d052075d3285e1451db2cb

ready for review.

commit_message:
Did not find the volume after live_migration

I migration the VM to another host, but there is a error occured when
source host excute the driver's live_migration. In the live_migration
process, the BDM was detach from source host and attach int dest, after
this step , the error occres, the nova-compute rollback the BDM, it detach
in dest, but didn't attach in source host.

Change-Id: If7c3d2c2db5b79ead62819a97f2b978bda9c7656
Closes-Bug: #1365804

commit_message:
Improve Ironic driver performance: patch 6

As part of some large scale operational testing, some needed
performance improvements in the ironic driver have been
identified.  These changes have been reviewed and have been
merged into the ironic tree previously (reviews 108545 & 113036)

Change-Id: I635b974353a9dee542739857aa9778bf1e78cca8
Co-authored-by: Jim Rollenhagen <jim@jimrollenhagen.com>
Co-authored-by: Chris Behrens <cbehrens@codestud.com>

commit_message:
Oslo Sync - Fix to mask passwords exception and error messages

This sync is primarily being done to pull in commits for
processutils and strutils to mask passwords better

strutils:

66142c3	Make strutils.mask_password more secure

processutils:

6a60f84	Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages
63c99a0	Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages
e184dd3	Fix exception message in openstack.common.processutils.execute
d6b55fb	Remove `processutils` dependency on `log`


Closes-Bug: #1343604
Change-Id: I98c09bb0570c2b507896faa25942a98e1d4f3867

commit_message:
Leave a symlink when to at /var/lib/cinder

When registering /var/lib/cinder as a state-path leave a symlink
to avoid cinder (installed from package) trying to recreate the
directory(which it doesn't have permission todo).

Change-Id: Ia14882c7a761687db69a1335c280302ac2d04c97

commit_message:
Fix up os-collect-config.conf on the seed

Move the creation of os-collect-config.conf on the seed to
11-seed-stack-heat-metadata so it happens after 10-os-collect-config
(and doesn't get overwriten).
Also change case of the default section to DEFAULT, oslo.config requires
it to be uppercase.

Change-Id: I6b75d448384e1647f8414765c8122460e6c28e60

Import Ironic Driver & supporting files - part 4

Import the Ironic virt driver and supporting files (driver part 2 -
validation, spawn, destroy, further getters), as well as relevant
unit tests, as of commit da967d77894be6f23d81fb5cc948f9d13898ba84

This is the dicing up of review/103167 into smaller chunks
ready for review.

Incorporating the bug fix https://review.openstack.org/#/c/118189

commit_message:
Moved context creation to benchmark.engine

Before this patch, context was created in benchmark.runner
base. This patch moved context creation to benchmark.engine.

This change makes the architecture of Rally much cleaner.
e.g. runners don't know anything about benchmark context
(removing one dependency in code)

In addition, getting named meta information from benchmark.
scenarios.base will return a deepcopy to prevent accidental
changes of the returned object.

Change-Id: I18277e6759a27ed0ec221620b2963cc35bdc2c32

commit_message:
Ironic driver backports: patch 7

The patch to remove the dependency on python-ironicclient was
misplaced in the split of 103167 into the series of smaller
patches that we're now reviewing.  This patch reinstates this
change so ironicclient is loaded dynamically, and does not
become a requirement for Nova when not using Ironic.

Change-Id: I70a2fa8fc45e18524ea4d777d72da24d5d329c25
Co-authored-by: Devananda van der Veen <devananda.vdv@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Revert "Provide an upgrade period for enabling stores"

This reverts commit b82e0b2c6fb1b34f7bf56b3cba8b7abc38022b8c.

Ie784fe90003a5064aaf16fadb7266bf7a46e2cf5 introduced a grace upgrade
period, enabling all stores by default. This was supposed to get
disabled for Juno.

Change-Id: Icb4c247c4be8e9001ae956b05e61ca643f3e7ccd

commit_message:
Adds the clients and tests for CINDER QoS V1 & V2 APIs

This patch adds the JSON clients and tests for following
CINDER QoS-specs V1 & V2 APIs :

1. qos-create
2. qos-delete
3. qos-list
4. qos-get
5. qos-key
6. qos-associate
7. qos-get-association
8. qos-disassociate
9. qos-disassociate-all

Partially Implements blueprint: client-checks-success
Partially Implements blueprint: cinder-v2-api-tests

Co-authored-by: Abhijeet.Jain <abhijeet.jain@nectechnologies.in>

Change-Id: I7fc424b57e4e8decf61e991b2988e1cead5dda9b

commit_message:
Validation check if exceeding vol snapshot quota

Disables "Create Snapshot" action for each volume in the Volumes table,
if the Volume Snapshot Quota is already at max.
Appends "Quota Exceeded" to the action button for user feedback.
Extends "test_get_data" to account for new Cinder api call.
Adds "test_create_snapshot_button_disabled_when_quota_exceeded"
to make sure action button state is altered when snapshots used is equal
to max snapshots.

Change-Id: I56798869f5e870cef2dd81301330b83aade040d4
Closes-Bug: 1333481

This patch is supposed to fix the bug 'Unable to delete domain if user
from other domain was added', but because of the recent changes this
should be done by configuring domain-specifc LDAPs. However the original
scenario must not be reproducible.

The rule is that if you have the standard LDAP driver for identity
(without configuring domain-specifc LDAPs), then you can really only
have the default domain. However currently it's possible to create
domains with the folowing configuration:

[identity]
driver = keystone.identity.backends.ldap.Identity
[assignment]
driver = keystone.assignment.backends.sql.Assignment

At the same time such new domains can not be updated nor deleted. This
fix prevents new domains creation for such configuration.

Also this fix adds an additional test to MultiLDAPandSQLIdentity to make
sure that the original bug has gone.

commit_message:
Prevent domains creation for the default LDAP+SQL

This patch is supposed to fix the bug 'Unable to delete domain if user
from other domain was added', but because of the recent changes this
should be done by configuring domain-specifc LDAPs. However the original
scenario must not be reproducible.

The rule is that if you have the standard LDAP driver for identity
(without configuring domain-specifc LDAPs), then you can really only
have the default domain. However currently it's possible to create
domains with the folowing configuration:

[identity]
driver = keystone.identity.backends.ldap.Identity
[assignment]
driver = keystone.assignment.backends.sql.Assignment

At the same time such new domains can not be updated nor deleted. This
fix prevents new domains creation for such configuration.

Also this fix adds an additional test to MultiLDAPandSQLIdentity to make
sure that the original bug has gone.

Closes-Bug: #1262360

Change-Id: I3baee40f74cefaae601aea34e75630cc618ac31a

commit_message:
Move driver unittest modules to proper place

It is expected, that unittests cover project modules in relation 1:1 and
placed in appropriate tree as main modules do.

It should be like in example:
manila/[tests/]foo/bar/[test_]modulename.py

Also fixed stub of service_instance in generic driver test suite, it was
overwriting service instance manager class for whole test run. Problem
appears only with this commit because order of tests is changed here.

Change-Id: I26136b21f55fb2563f15a9a44ca0b6613f75165c
Partial-Bug: #1348633

commit_message:
Move unittests related to manila/share/*.py modules to proper place

It is expected, that unittests cover project modules in relation 1:1 and
placed in appropriate tree as main modules do.

It should be like in example:
manila/[tests/]foo/bar/[test_]modulename.py

Existing file 'manila/tests/test_share.py' will be merged with existing file
'manila/tests/share/test_manager.py' separately.

Change-Id: Ifd9dc13f4632b255dae81b521a05d47838b3042c
Partial-Fix: #1348633

commit_message:
Fix: Redis driver does not fall back to default port

The Redis driver requires a port in the URI string read from the
Zaqar configuration. However, it is common practice to fall back
to a default port in connection URIs, so this patch implements
support for that in the spirit of the Principle of Least Suprise.

Change-Id: I3205890bbd10b49b1be59f4465617214881e6cc0

[{'created': '2014-09-09 03:40:53.000000000', 'message': "Update Zaqar backend requirements

MongoDB is not Zaqar's default storage backend.
In fact, Zaqar don't have a default storage backend.
Considering this, pymongo shouldn't be in requirements.txt.
We still need it for the tests environments though.

Documentation about this situation will be added in the developers

commit_message:
Update Zaqar backend requirements

MongoDB is not Zaqar's default storage backend.
In fact, Zaqar don't have a default storage backend.
Considering this, pymongo shouldn't be in requirements.txt.
We still need it for the tests environments though.

Documentation about this situation will be added in the developers
guide and in the users guide in a follow up patch.

Change-Id: Ia9e039c671274fa32d90d8c31be6dca4d47bcbaf

commit_message:
Adds the API reference to the devs guide

This fix adds the detailed API reference to the developers guide
as it's done in major projects in the stack.

It also fix Sphinx warning and errors and adds a .rst files
generator to easily update the api reference in the future.

Plus, it includes an index for API, modules and search.

Co-Authored-By: Flavio Percoco <fpercoco@redhat.com>

Change-Id: If42121c9e8e852785cb2db3aa5d6895223b9d604

commit_message:
Use Token fixtures from keystoneclient

Keystoneclient provides a way of generating correctly formed tokens. We
should test using those rather than things we copy and paste ourselves.

Change-Id: I163940c3cd92060f68e9b1149865feeef0480e6e

Implemented RPC messaging

API and processors now talk via oslo.messaging.
Updated openstack-common to add lockutils support.

Change-Id: I0b06a8c8b6612eda6a2ff8785a4f0d516347f09a

commit_message:
Cinder Client for Consistency Groups

This patch implements CLI commands for the Consistency Groups
feature. Only snapshots for CGs will be implemented in phase 1.

Change-Id: I447555fd8a92bceecf6f40be59030d65461e4cbb
Implements: blueprint consistency-groups

commit_message:
Import Ironic Driver & supporting files - part 1

Import the Ironic virt driver and supporting files (client lib wrapper
and state mapping), as well as relevant unit tests, as of commit
da967d77894be6f23d81fb5cc948f9d13898ba84

This is the dicing up of review/103167 into smaller chunks
ready for review.

commit_message:
Stop tracking connections in DVR FIP Namespace

For DVR, connections to external network using floating IPs do not
need to be tracked in FIP namespace because they are being
already tracked in router namespace.
This fix adds iptable rules to not track connections.

Change-Id: I378039e311763d114860cb70ded7349d6580855a
Closes-bug: #1360395

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-07 17:36:25.000000000', 'message': "Fix possible race condition for accept transfer

Accept transfer API workflow is currently like this:

  call volume_api.accept_transfer()
    |
    --- RPC cast to volume manager
          |
          --- volume manager calls volume driver accept_transfer()

  update volume's DB record

Given the non-blocking nature of RPC cast, what happens in volume
manager and volume driver can happen in parallel with the DB update.
If volume driver relies on original DB record to do things, then
DB record shouldn't be updated until volume driver finishes its job.

So this patch change volume RPC API accept_transfer() from cast
to call to make sure the workflow is in serialied manner.

Change-Id: Ieae52e167aa02967338e0be5d78d570d682faa7a
Closes-bug: #1357432
"}, {'created': '2014-09-08 04:30:31.000000000', 'message': "Fix possible race condition for accept transfer

manager and volume driver can happen in parallel with the DB update.

commit_message:
Fix possible race condition for accept transfer

Accept transfer API workflow is currently like this:

  call volume_api.accept_transfer()
    |
    --- RPC cast to volume manager
          |
          --- volume manager calls volume driver accept_transfer()

  update volume's DB record

Given the non-blocking nature of RPC cast, what happens in volume
manager and volume driver can happen in parallel with the DB update.
If volume driver relies on original DB record to do things, then
DB record shouldn't be updated until volume driver finishes its job.

So this patch change volume RPC API accept_transfer() from cast
to call to make sure the workflow is in serialized manner.  Also
elevated the context when volume manager tries to update the DB
record when driver has done accept_transfer().

Change-Id: Ieae52e167aa02967338e0be5d78d570d682faa7a
Closes-bug: #1357432

commit_message:
crontab to move deleted instance rows to another database table

Create a crontab which moves deleted instances rows to another database table that you don't have to backup.
This is done to optimize database management at scale.
Depending on the amount of deleted instances that you get on a daily
basis you want to modify the $max_rows parameter.

This feature is implemented as in nova CLI and addressed by this
blueprint: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/db-archiving

Change-Id: Ia03fa6862aefcbcc7d7949b08d00bacf679cb548
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Renaming in WalkVersionsMixin

Rename _walk_versions(), _migrate_up(), _migrate_down()
and mark them deprecated as they will be removed in few
releases. These functions will be the part of public API
as this class will be used for migrations in other
OpenStack projects, so there is no need to make them
'private'.

Change-Id: Ic9358445e60a0dd43a5900e8bda7b12f2bebf679

commit_message:

* Added DB API methods for actions
* Unit tests
* Refactored action_manager to use db_api.load_action() method
* Minor refactoring

commit_message:
Creating ad-hoc actions engine test

* Added a test for workflow using an ad-hoc action
* Fixed action manager to allow action names without "."
* Fixed action manager unit tests
* Added utility methods to engine test base class

Change-Id: I6a26a8b1e6f5a8a954ba5270658bec77851c7841

Hey Zhi Yan,

I'm not sold on the use case explained in the commit message. Could you please elaborate more on what you want to achieve with this?

I don't like the idea of glance messing with FS permissions. There are a couple of reasons:

1. We've tenants to handle this
2. Glance doesn't own the data and having control over the permissions implies that Glance is the owner of that data.

thanks"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-21 10:14:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Verified

commit_message:
Allowing operator to configure a permission for image file in fs store

In this way the user other service used, e.g. Nova, who consumes the
image could be the exclusive member of the group that owns the files
created.

Closes-bug: 1264302
Change-Id: I4d543d205b0805fe00dcab1b0872c0a5e0f97a5f
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Heat SwiftResources : only count containers created by Tempest

Some containers in the demo tenant could be there before the Tempest
run so we should exclude them when we count containers created by
the stack.

Change-Id: I20ae92e8cc2b61197774963d049fd8231dafdb56
Closes-Bug: 1360832

[{'created': '2014-09-07 20:11:15.000000000', 'message': 'Setup for translation

To start translation, we need to initially import the
translation file - and place it at the proper place so that
the usual CI scripts can handle it.

The proper place is for all python projects
$PROJECT/locale/$PROJECT.pot - see setup.cfg.

Further imports will be done by the OpenStack Proposal bot.

Change-Id: I29b9fe0c286d1f54c260bff0569ea3e4e8092c3c
'}]
commit_message:
Setup for translation

To start translation, we need to initially import the
translation file - and place it at the proper place so that
the usual CI scripts can handle it.

The proper place is for all python projects
$PROJECT/locale/$PROJECT.pot - see setup.cfg.

Further imports will be done by the OpenStack Proposal bot.

Change-Id: I29b9fe0c286d1f54c260bff0569ea3e4e8092c3c

commit_message:
Make function err run echo with root

Currently trying to write to the file ${SCREEN_LOGDIR}/error.log,
results in a permission denied. So wrap this line in a sudo.

Change-Id: I0a99b753c1d0200be4ead7449ab9a355994081a5

back port: icehouse

commit_message:
Update the HP 3PAR default persona

This updates the change in the OpenStack Configuration Reference Guide to
match the merged code (https://review.openstack.org/118500).
The new default for the hp3par:persona should be '2 - Generic-ALUA'.

Change-Id: I4d79ed62a6fe6ed09231b584c96b7a552ee2fb6e
Closes-bug: 1365696

Support for copying streamOptimized disk to file

This patch adds a method for copying virtual disk in streamOptimized
format from VMware datastore to a file.

Change-Id: I1e358e6fe310312515bdcdf014f8beaf7a82256d

Update transitioning function name to be more understandable

To make it more obvious what this function does adjust the naming
to be more clear and add a docstring that explains this in more
depth.

commit_message:
Modifies example command for nova network-create

The example given for creating networks in the Networking
concepts page in the OpenStack Cloud Administrator Guide
has an error. The --fixed-cidr should be a subset of the
--fixed-range-v4, but the example fixed-cidr is both larger
and part of a different network.

This fix corrects the subnet sizes and changes the network
addresses on both --fixed-range-v4 and --fixed-cidr to make
--fixed-cidr a valid subnet of --fixed-range-v4.

Change-Id: Ibb933bea845dee6cd1a5f0559e392820ff376a84
Closes-Bug: #1366214

commit_message:
Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages

When a ProcessExecutionError is thrown by processutils.execute(), the
exception may contain information such as password. Upstream
applications that just log the message (as several appear to do) could
inadvertently expose these passwords to a user with read access to the
log files. It is therefore considered prudent to invoke
strutils.mask_password() on the command, stdout and stderr in the
exception.

Cherry-pick from review.openstack.org/109417
Partial-Bug: #1343604

Change-Id: I9741dcdebdb4bed295ddc5ec4c4b117fffcfe88c

commit_message:
Remove subnet_id from check_ports_exist_on_l3agent

Refactor check_ports_exist_on_l3agent so that subnet_id no longer
needs to be passed.  Instead it calls get_subnet_ids_on_router.  This
helps to pave the way for removing hints from schedule router.

Partial-bug: #1353266
Partial-bug: #1356639
Co-Authored-By: Swaminathan Vasudevan <swaminathan.vasudevan@hp.com>

Change-Id: I6e9dcb0b899294bb4cf3e3d616a0a690049c338e

commit_message:
Leverage openstack.common.jsonutils

This patch removes our own home brewed json helper functions and leverages
the ones from openstack.common.jsonutils instead.

Change-Id: Idc5ee0fec56b0a0f337433a830647d4f421a8283
Closes-bug: 1365263

[{'created': '2014-06-27 09:50:48.000000000', 'message': "API support for random access to images

This patch adds support for random access to images to the API v2. It's
possible to partially access the image data by passing the offset where
the image should be fetched from and the size of the chunk expected.

Note that not all stores support random access to image data. In such
cases, the API will return an error mentioning the selected store
doesn't support such a feature.

DO NOT MERGE: Tests and error handling missing.

Implements blueprint: restartable-image-download

Change-Id: Iade692a8197a9a1d9532711a5c572c505e5e7d20

commit_message:
API support for random access to images

This patch adds support for random access to images to the API v2. It's
possible to partially access the image data by passing the offset where
the image should be fetched from and the size of the chunk expected.

Note that not all stores support random access to image data. In such
cases, the API will return an error mentioning the selected store
doesn't support such a feature.

DocImpact:
Content-Range header is now parsed to support random access to image
data.

Implements blueprint: restartable-image-download

Change-Id: Iade692a8197a9a1d9532711a5c572c505e5e7d20

commit_message:
Allow devstack to build ironic agent ramdisk

This provides a way to test Ironic-python-agent code that is
not yet merged.

Change-Id: I85084c383263173a33250592a95a17f46827b347

[{'created': '2014-08-27 15:56:47.000000000', 'message': "Update DVR Binding when router_id changes

When a new router namespace is created on a host, sync_router
will call _ensure_host_set_on_port that will update the DVR binding.
With the current code update_dvr_port_binding won't update the
binding if there's an existing binding unless the binding
vif_type is VIF_TYPE_BINDING_FAILED . There's a race when
the router namespace is destroyed and then recreated on the same
host.
The DVR binding is deleted only when the message
update_device_down is processed. If this message is processed
after the update_dvr_port_binding triggered by the namespace creation,
update_dvr_port_binding won't update the binding. When the router
interface will be detected as UP, no DVR binding will be found.

In this patch I modified update_dvr_port_binding to update the
binding if router_id changes. I removed the code to update the
binding in dvr_deletens_if_no_vm, since this will be done now in
update_dvr_port_binding .

Change-Id: I37fd4ed67dc2019b57e36d082b584c517d8f67a8

commit_message:
Update DVR Binding when router_id changes

In this patch I modified update_dvr_port_binding to update the
binding if router_id changes.
When a new router namespace is created on a host, sync_router
will call _ensure_host_set_on_port that will update the DVR binding.
With the current code update_dvr_port_binding won't update the
binding if there's an existing binding unless the binding
vif_type is VIF_TYPE_BINDING_FAILED . There's a race when
the router namespace is destroyed and then recreated on the same
host.
The DVR binding is deleted only when the message
update_device_down is processed. If this message is processed
after the update_dvr_port_binding triggered by the namespace creation,
update_dvr_port_binding won't update the binding. When the router
interface will be detected as UP, no DVR binding will be found.

Closes-bug: #1358554
Change-Id: I37fd4ed67dc2019b57e36d082b584c517d8f67a8

commit_message:
Fix oauth sqlite migration downgrade failure

The oauth migration downgrade was failing because it tried to drop
a constraint which sqlite doesn't support. The code tried to not do
the drop on sqlite but didn't check for the sqlite engine properly.

Change-Id: Ie7900d352a26900f913bdefe1eb93d511283efc0
Closes-Bug: #1366606

commit_message:
Update oslo-incubator to 32e7f0b56f52742754

Pickup a couple of changes (mainly the first one listed below)
that are useful to have before we release and will ensure
we are compatible with python 2.6 and RHEL due to a bug
in jsonutils.

d9060f69d203 - Check for namedtuple_as_object support before using it
66142c3471fe - Make strutils.mask_password more secure

Closes-Bug: #1361230

commit_message:
Fix tests with testtools>=0.9.39

NOTE: the RPC module that was causing problems in Icehouse no longer
exists in master, but the fix should be in the master as well to avoid
future problems.

'rpc_backend' config option in
ceilometer.openstack.common.rpc.__init__.py defaults to
'%s.impl_kombu' % __package__. Because the RPC module is imported
in some other files as ceilometer.openstack.common.rpc, rpc_backend
is set to 'ceilometer.openstack.common.rpc.impl_kombu'. But when
the test loader tries to import the RPC module as openstack.common.rpc
(since it is starting inside the ceilometer folder), registering the
option fails, because we try to register a different default value.

The issue surfaced because testtools==0.9.39 started checking __init__.py
files as well. It is fixed by passing a top-level directory parameter to
the test discovery process.

(cherry picked from commit 7ff220fc5cb4dad616b27ea6762653054df00139)

Conflicts:
	.testr.conf

Change-Id: I08036b54def3eb496772bcf183927b9f70bb7a86
Closes-bug: #1365613

commit_message:
Use explicit WBE request state transitions

Instead of having an implicit state machine for a requests
lifecycle move toward an explicit state model and transition
set that is validated and transitioned in a more easy to
understand/reason about manner.

This also fixes a bug that was found due to a response validation
not taking into account a transition that was found due to this
stricter transition checking.

Includes a few tiny related/affected commits:

* Remove testing of request repr() and str() as these types of
  tests are not useful and we removed the repr() version of the
  request message as the base classes is good enough.
* Raise and capture a better exception and save its associated
  failure object when a request has expired (this gives expired
  requests better failure objects and associated details).

Fixes bug 1356658

Partially fixes bug 1357117

Change-Id: Ie1386cca13a2da7265e22447b4c111a0a0074201

commit_message:
remove object in wsgi LOG.info

Method __init__ in Server class records log for wsgi server name, host
and port using its __dict__ which includes a socket object. i18n message
will deep copy each item's value in __dict__. In python2.6, deep copy
the socket object will raise "Exception RuntimeError" and can not be
caught. This makes cinder-api run into a hang loop. This patch uses the
related properties instead of __dict__ object to fix the problem.

Closes-Bug: #1365901
Change-Id: Ia6ac51f4849d369c54ac88b1587741a2d2beb40b

'}, {'account_id': 3211, 'date': '2014-04-17 02:09:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

@Ray Chen

When we send delete request to nova, nova change vm`s statu to deleting and then send the message from nova-api to nova-compute throught rabbitmq. While ,if rabbitmq crashed, the message maybe lost, it cause the delete operation cannot be executed. Then ,use 'nova list' command, we can see the vm`s statu would be deleting and would not change forever. If we send nova delete command once more, because the older codes dropped duplicate delete requests, we cannot recycling resources from these vms which would be deleted.

If we remove the older codes, means nova can receive and handle duplicate delete requests, the delete operation can be execute correctly.

In havana ,we can do this like above, So i remove those codes"}, {'account_id': 10500, 'date': '2014-04-17 02:33:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

@zhangjl, your words look like to prove that we need the codes you removed. if multipath requests come in in short time, we should drop duped delete request duing vm state is in DELETEING. 

it's not reasonable to rollback to Havana version just because it works once."}, {'account_id': 3211, 'date': '2014-04-17 02:54:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Ray Chen

I do not agree with you.
Is it means any vm can be deleted once ?
How to ensure vm can be delete established if we only can send delete request once?
If the delete request lost but the vm statu had been changed to deleting, How to recycling resources?

In my view, to handle request come in in short time , we can set the limitations ,while ,it`s not the reason that drop or ignore duplicate delete requests which not come in in short time.

I hope you think more about the above.'}, {'account_id': 1004, 'date': '2014-04-17 04:27:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I don't think delete's should be sent twice to the compute node because they don't expect it.

If the scenario you explained happened, you can simply do this:

nova reset-state --active <uuid>
nova delete <uuid>"}, {'account_id': 3211, 'date': '2014-04-17 05:43:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

@Mohammed Naser

First, the 'scenario' i explained is not scenario, it really occured in my openstack environment at least twice.

Second, use nova reset-state first then use nova delete can 
solve the question above. While, if there were hundreds vms ,
I do not think use nova reset-state and nova delete both is better than use nova delete only.

Thanks for your reply."}, {'account_id': 6062, 'date': '2014-04-17 07:22:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Agree with Mohammed Naser

compute layer don't expect the delete request sent more than once, if you do think you need to handle this function, you also need to consider changes and exception handling in compute layer

and your mentioned rabbitmq issue, I think under this circumstance, the whole system might have issue and services such as compute service might need to be restarted, a compute resize will remove the instances stuck in deleting"}, {'account_id': 6062, 'date': '2014-04-17 07:22:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Cannot delete vm instance if send duplicate delete requests

When We delete many vm instances at the same time,
because of many reasons, the delete requests and
messages maybe lost or droped by rabbitmq when
transported from nova-api to nova-compute. While,
the vms statu had been changed to deleting in
database .Then, if we send duplicate delete requests,
it would be ignored, then the vms cannot be deleted,
it cause we cannot recycling resources from vms
which should be deleted but not. To fix this problem,
change the method _delete to the havana version.

Change-Id: I723c27f8bf9cf5682dc9501d6cbd1046230f62a3
Closes-bug: #1308342

commit_message:
Fix wrong parameter of new_image v2 API

Currently new_image v2 api is using wrong parameter 'image_id', which
will make '--id' option can't be set when creating an image.

Change-Id: I29d87abd0d87e9c7a6f361c1ff330ebd5293f4d1
Closes-Bug: #1367059

[{'created': '2014-08-25 22:59:20.000000000', 'message': 'Rally info: deploy engines & server providers

* Add support for searching for deploy engines & server providers in rally info
* Unify the docs for those classes so that all they contain config samples and
  have the same formatting style.

Change-Id: I9a4ae51d01bff155ba22c68f86666c8896eacc44
'}, {'created': '2014-08-25 23:02:58.000000000', 'message': 'Rally info: deploy engines & server providers

* Add support for searching for deploy engines & server providers in rally info
* Unify the docs for those classes so that all they contain config samples and
  have the same formatting style.

Usage sample:

    $ rally info find ExistingServers
    ExistingServers (server provider).

    Just return endpoints from its own configuration.

    Sample configuration:

        {
            "type": "ExistingServers",
            "credentials": [{"user": "root", "host": "localhost"}]
        }

    $ rally info find DevstackEngine
    DevstackEngine (deploy engine).

    Deploy Devstack cloud.

    Sample configuration:

        {
            "type": "DevstackEngine",
            "devstack_repo": "https://example.com/devstack/",
            "localrc": {
                "ADMIN_PASSWORD": "secret"
            },
            "provider": {
                "type": "ExistingServers",
                "credentials": [{'user': 'root', 'host': '10.2.0.8'}]
            }
        }

Change-Id: I9a4ae51d01bff155ba22c68f86666c8896eacc44

commit_message:
Rally info: deploy engines & server providers

* Add support for searching for deploy engines & server providers in rally info
* Unify the docs for those classes so that all they contain config samples and
  have the same formatting style.

Usage sample:

    $ rally info find ExistingServers
    ExistingServers (server provider).

    Just return endpoints from its own configuration.

    Sample configuration:

        {
            "type": "ExistingServers",
            "credentials": [{"user": "root", "host": "localhost"}]
        }

    $ rally info find DevstackEngine
    DevstackEngine (deploy engine).

    Deploy Devstack cloud.

    Sample configuration:

        {
            "type": "DevstackEngine",
            "devstack_repo": "https://example.com/devstack/",
            "localrc": {
                "ADMIN_PASSWORD": "secret"
            },
            "provider": {
                "type": "ExistingServers",
                "credentials": [{'user': 'root', 'host': '10.2.0.8'}]
            }
        }

Change-Id: I9a4ae51d01bff155ba22c68f86666c8896eacc44

commit_message:
Return the right filesize when chunk_size != None

The filesystem store kept returning the full file size even when
chunk_size was not None. This patch fixes that issue.

Change-Id: Ifa7d08cabe4485e1f9f4bf2d21ce7e307236104b

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-17 17:33:59.000000000', 'message': "Adopt glance.store library in Glance

This commits removes the old `store` package from glance and adopts the
usage of the new glance.store library. The library was designed to
preserve backwards compatibility as much as possible. In fact, most of
the changes in this patch are related to function args ordering and not
function renames or workflow changes.

Some changes that are worth mentioning:

1. Glance store doesn't rely on a global config object. All config
options must be explicitly registered.

2. All store operations now accepted an optional context. This is a
fallout from the context not being required in the `Store` constructor
anymore.

3. Store drivers are behind a private package called `_drivers` and
they're not suppose to be accessed directly. Instead, functions like
`get_store_from_scheme` should be used.

4. Stores are disabled by default

5. All the store specific options are under the `glance_store` group.

Change-Id: Iaacc70993ad5da292b93de42bbecda73d53b19fd

commit_message:
Adopt glance.store library in Glance

This commits removes the old `store` package from glance and adopts the
usage of the new glance.store library. The library was designed to
preserve backwards compatibility as much as possible. In fact, most of
the changes in this patch are related to function args ordering and not
function renames or workflow changes.

Some changes that are worth mentioning:

1. Glance store doesn't rely on a global config object. All config
options must be explicitly registered.

2. All store operations now accepted an optional context. This is a
fallout from the context not being required in the `Store` constructor
anymore.

3. Store drivers are behind a private package called `_drivers` and
they're not suppose to be accessed directly. Instead, functions like
`get_store_from_scheme` should be used.

4. Stores are disabled by default

5. All the store specific options are under the `glance_store` group.

DocImpact:
The old store related configuration options have been moved under the
`glance_store` section. However, the old options will go through a
deprecation path. That is, they'll still be read from the `DEFAULT`
section to give deployers enough time to update their config files.

In k-2, the deprecated options will be completely obsolete.

Closes-bug: #1291848
Implements-blueprint: create-store-package

Change-Id: Iaacc70993ad5da292b93de42bbecda73d53b19fd

commit_message:
Make strutils.mask_password more secure

Make some enhancements to strutils.mask_password to allow it to
catch more cases of passwords in strings.

The following is a listing of patterns that will be handled. The
keyword that mask_password uses (a list of four now) is represented
by <key> and the password is shown as <password>. Quotes (both single
and double) are represented as <quote>.

--<key> <password>
--<key> <quote><password><quote>
<key> = <password>
<key> = <quote><password><quote>

All existing tests and patterns are still handled.

Cherry-pick from review.openstack.org/113407
Partial-Bug: #1345233

Change-Id: I693baaf225c5b393401d499d14f271cadb63eb2c

commit_message:
WIP: VMware: image fetch/cache functions

To more cleanly support the various permutations of the following during
spawn():
- different types image to spawn with (sparse, flat, iso,
  and streamOptimized, ova in the futre)
- different ways to obtain the image (http download, and direct
  datastore copy in the future)
- different ways to prepare the downloaded image bits into a usable
  image in the image cache (replace -flat.vmdk extent, convert from
  sparse, pick from imported VM, ...)

The following are introduced:
- Image prepare/fetch/cache functions : these are callbacks for
  processing the bits into a usable form to be cached in the image cache
  under various scenarios.
- Image fetching functions : these are callbacks called by the processor
  to obtain the bits for the hypervisor.

This should will allow for more self-contained additions/changes
to behaviors in these areas in the future.

blueprint vmware-spawn-refactor
Change-Id: I9bc5a028d1cca3bbc30a67ae27e42c95eeacc013

commit_message:
Add new command to run dsvm-gate-tests

This command is added to run the devstack VM gate tests under
OpenStack CI. The entrypoint will be a devstack-vm-gate setup.
The script handles setting up test configuration through kick-start,
and actually running the Trove tests.

Change-Id: I78471d7f11d0f1a23e2efc28da2e62c5707e575a

commit_message:
Rollback master backend on all exceptions in multi backend

Some exceptions passed out of backends are not Designate exceptions,
these exceptions are not caught in the multi backend, causing the
rollback code not to be executed.

Change-Id: I9f29b06dcca5ea03f522ae392401ce8b34121e34
Closes-Bug: 1293101

[{'created': '2014-09-08 12:50:19.000000000', 'message': "Fix race conditions running pxe_utils tests in parallel

To avoid the race this patch is mocking the DHCPFactory.provider
attribute instead of mocking a specific provider implementation (Neutron
before). The DHCPFactory is a complex class because it's a singleton,
and by mocking a specific provider and not the top level class tests
could override each other.

Closes-Bug: #1365370
Change-Id: I9b1bd69b73606a4b2665170ae076742c0bac68da
"}]
commit_message:
Fix race conditions running pxe_utils tests in parallel

To avoid the race this patch is mocking the DHCPFactory.provider
attribute instead of mocking a specific provider implementation (Neutron
before). The DHCPFactory is a complex class because it's a singleton,
and by mocking a specific provider and not the top level class tests
could override each other.

Closes-Bug: #1365370
Change-Id: I9b1bd69b73606a4b2665170ae076742c0bac68da

commit_message:
Makes kombu_ssl_* parameters optional when rabbit_use_ssl => true

The kombu_ssl_* parameters should not be required when rabbit_use_ssl => true
Rather, rabbit_use_ssl must be set to true if the kombu_ssl_* parameters are
used.

Change-Id: If9cceb4f4090c8b39079aa1aae2f53640c9ac0ff
Closes-Bug: 1356083

commit_message:
Makes kombu_ssl_* parameters optional when rabbit_use_ssl => true

The kombu_ssl_* parameters should not be required when rabbit_use_ssl => true
Rather, rabbit_use_ssl must be set to true if the kombu_ssl_* parameters are
used.

Change-Id: I7664dda2c66ffb34ceb56ada722574ae0e490f8f
Closes-Bug: 1356083

[{'created': '2014-01-16 12:32:29.000000000', 'message': 'Add templates for bootstrap's horizontal forms

Bootstrap's form-horizontal requires a little different HTML
structure than the default horiozn's field template uses. This
patch adds a _horizontal_fields.html template, that behaves like
the _form_fields.html template, only is suitable for use inside
a <form class="form-horizontal"> tag.

It also splits out the _form_errors.html, _form_field.html and

commit_message:
Add templates for bootstrap's horizontal forms

Bootstrap's form-horizontal requires a little different HTML
structure than the default horiozn's field template uses. This
patch adds a _horizontal_fields.html template, that behaves like
the _form_fields.html template, only is suitable for use inside
a <form class="form-horizontal"> tag.

It also splits out the _form_errors.html, _form_field.html and
_horizontal_field.html templates, so that it is easier to build custom
forms with fieldsets by including those for every field, instead of all
the fields at once.

Change-Id: I51c8f47ba230c6a78919979cc0ef4e2383d100ba
Implements: blueprint horizontal-form

commit_message:
Document authx feature, Phases I and II

user-guide
- cli.rst -- document fuel cli command to change
  password and flags to use with commands to supply password;
  fixed a couple typos while the file was open
- initialize-fuel/0400-pxe-config.rst -- added screen shot
  for setting password during Fuel Setup
- create-environment/1000-start-create-env.rst
  - Added Fuel login screen
  - Replaced initial Fuel screen to have "password" link showing
  - Added text and screen shot for modifying password

ops-guide -- 6500-fuel-auth -- explain authorization functionality

release-notes -- 020-new-features -- added link to ops guide info,
which includes links to the other docs

terminology -- updated keystone article to point to password stuff

Change-Id: I6d2c515b6200be2307bf78b6c0a202e958d51220
Closes-Bug: 1348750

commit_message:
Makes kombu_ssl_* parameters optional when rabbit_use_ssl => true

The kombu_ssl_* parameters should not be required when rabbit_use_ssl => true
Rather, rabbit_use_ssl must be set to true if the kombu_ssl_* parameters are
used.

(Similar to this patch to puppet-neutron: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/113671/ )

Closes-Bug: 1356083
Change-Id: I6a27ebf359c1910e221e9dc31711c6af569dc0ce

'}, {'created': '2014-08-01 18:39:52.000000000', 'message': "Glance Metadata Definitions Catalog

A common API hosted by the Glance service for vendors, admins,
services, and users to meaningfully define available key / value
pair and tag metadata. The intent is to enable better metadata
collaboration across artifacts, services, and projects for
OpenStack users.

This is about the definition of the available metadata that can
be used on different types of resources (images, artifacts,
volumes, flavors, aggregates, etc). A definition includes the
properties type, its key, it's description, and it's constraints.
This catalog will not store the values for specific instance
properties.

WORK IN PROGRESS

Currently committed:
 - DB migrate version (glance-manage db sync)
 - DB data seeding (glance-manage db load_metadefs)
 - DB CRUD on tag, namespace and metadata objects.
 - REST API for CRUD on namespace and metadata objects.
 - REST API for CRUD on tags (draft).
 - REST API for JSON schemas of namespaces, objects and tags.
 - In Progress Namespaces
 - In Progress Simple DB API

commit_message:
Glance Metadata Definitions Catalog

A common API hosted by the Glance service for vendors, admins,
services, and users to meaningfully define available key / value
pair and tag metadata. The intent is to enable better metadata
collaboration across artifacts, services, and projects for
OpenStack users.

This is about the definition of the available metadata that can
be used on different types of resources (images, artifacts,
volumes, flavors, aggregates, etc). A definition includes the
properties type, its key, it's description, and it's constraints.
This catalog will not store the values for specific instance
properties.

WORK IN PROGRESS

Currently committed:
 - DB migrate version (glance-manage db sync)
 - DB data seeding (glance-manage db load_metadefs)
 - DB CRUD on tag, namespace and metadata objects.
 - REST API for CRUD on namespace and metadata objects.
 - REST API for CRUD on tags (draft).
 - REST API for JSON schemas of namespaces, objects and tags.
 - In Progress Namespaces
 - In Progress Simple DB API

Change-Id: I0ab79eaa0e5a2059e7c3abdeed97a8b641b7e25c

commit_message:
Make neutronapi use NetworkRequest for allocate_for_instance()

This makes the neutronapi code use the NetworkRequest object for
the allocate_for_instance() operation. It also prepares validate_networks()
by using the object internally, which will make it easier when we
actually start passing that from the caller.

Change-Id: I71c85ed4124e1e00b8c4c6d8dc02f2f280d69cfa

A few of the LDAP searches performed in the identity and assignment
LDAP drivers do not specify the list of attributes to return, which
causes all attributes present in the LDAP entry to be returned.  We
attempt to convery these values from utf8 to unicode, which fails
when we encounter a binary value.  This patch addresses this problem
in two ways.

The first is to only request the attributes that we actually need
returned from the LDAP server.  This avoids potential binary values
that we do not even need to be concerned with.

The second thing this patch does is to make our conversion code
more tolerant by ignoring attributes that contain binary values.  If
a binary value is present, we simply skip over that attribute in
the conversion and log a debug message.  We should not be encounting
binary values in a typical Keystone deployment, but this gives us
some protection just in case we do encounter a binary value.

Closes-bug: #1355489

commit_message:
Avoid conversion of binary LDAP values

A few of the LDAP searches performed in the identity and assignment
LDAP drivers do not specify the list of attributes to return, which
causes all attributes present in the LDAP entry to be returned.  We
attempt to convery these values from utf8 to unicode, which fails
when we encounter a binary value.  This patch addresses this problem
in two ways.

The first is to only request the attributes that we actually need
returned from the LDAP server.  This avoids potential binary values
that we do not even need to be concerned with.

The second thing this patch does is to make our conversion code
more tolerant by ignoring attributes that contain binary values.  If
a binary value is present, we simply skip over that attribute in
the conversion and log a debug message.  We should not be encounting
binary values in a typical Keystone deployment, but this gives us
some protection just in case we do encounter a binary value.

Closes-bug: #1355489
Change-Id: I62325ab9c75bac67cca329fb7bd3c74aea7d2867

commit_message:
mock.assert_called_once() is not a valid method

mock.assert_called_once() is a no-op that tests nothing.  Instead
with mock.assert_called_once_with() should be used (or use
assertEqual(1, mock_obj.call_count) if you don't want to check
parameters).

Change-Id: Ib302f2e888306558535cdd3e5edf447809aee430
Partial-Bug: #1365751

[{'created': '2014-09-05 21:23:32.000000000', 'message': "Pay attention to all punctual nodes

The proxy sends requests to all storage nodes, but it only needs a
quorum of them to respond before the proxy can, in turn, respond to
the client. Thus, it gets quorum, and then briefly waits to see if the
remainder of the storage nodes respond before giving up on them.

However, the proxy was not paying any attention to the responses from
the non-quorum storage nodes. This would lead to some odd behavior,
like a container PUT where the backends returned (201, 201, 202) would
become a 201 to the client, but the permutation (201, 202, 201) would
become 202. Further, on object PUT, if the last node responded with an
error code, that error wouldn't count towards error-limiting.

The fix is quite simple: after getting quorum, the make_requests()
method was calling a method that returns responses from the remainder
of the nodes, but it was ignoring that return value and making up
responses with dummy values instead. Now, prior to making up dummy
responses, the proxy first uses the responses it already has, and only
fills in dummy responses for nodes that really didn't respond in time.

Change-Id: I0206b6b2272b0e7dcc80fb6c51840d8dae25cee2
"}]
commit_message:
Pay attention to all punctual nodes

The proxy sends requests to all storage nodes, but it only needs a
quorum of them to respond before the proxy can, in turn, respond to
the client. Thus, it gets quorum, and then briefly waits to see if the
remainder of the storage nodes respond before giving up on them.

However, the proxy was not paying any attention to the responses from
the non-quorum storage nodes. This would lead to some odd behavior,
like a container PUT where the backends returned (201, 201, 202) would
become a 201 to the client, but the permutation (201, 202, 201) would
become 202. Further, on object PUT, if the last node responded with an
error code, that error wouldn't count towards error-limiting.

The fix is quite simple: after getting quorum, the make_requests()
method was calling a method that returns responses from the remainder
of the nodes, but it was ignoring that return value and making up
responses with dummy values instead. Now, prior to making up dummy
responses, the proxy first uses the responses it already has, and only
fills in dummy responses for nodes that really didn't respond in time.

Change-Id: I0206b6b2272b0e7dcc80fb6c51840d8dae25cee2

commit_message:
Explain groups for DeprecatedOpts

The patch extends the documentation for `DeprecatedOpt` and explains
that group==None means the deprecated name will be looked up in the same
group.

Change-Id: I54ba414d6a6862e1b00dfbf589563ef9f4df5cf3

commit_message:
Standardize usage of client arguments (user-guide)

Like documented at https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions#Client_arguments:_.22--option_ARGUMENT.22
we prefer to use '--option ARGUMENT'.

Change-Id: If0a33ca02cd499769d1540b74b1ab0a217c839d4

commit_message:
Change v3 quota-sets API to v2.1

This patch changes v3 quota-sets API to v2.1 and makes v2 unit tests
share between v2 and v2.1.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3 .

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I96377c2c5c02e00cb70eadde225f3e17d0e0025c

commit_message:
Use "--is-public True" during image-create's

A new glanceclient has been released that no longer supports the
--public option.

Change-Id: I8075271f894d16c9d090106b0d41ab9d3069400a
Closes-Bug: #1366808

commit_message:
Allowing operator to configure a permission for image file in fs store

In this way the user other service used, e.g. Nova, who consumes the
image could be the exclusive member of the group that owns the files
created.

Closes-bug: 1264302
Related-Id: I4d543d205b0805fe00dcab1b0872c0a5e0f97a5f
Change-Id: Iec8396f92ed11531dccb82957da2455ca333430a
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
_find_recordsets returns active recordsets only

_find_recordsets returns only active recordsets.
A join needs to be done, as the domains table has
a deleted column to indicate deleted domains but
the recordsets table does not have a deleted
column.

Change-Id: Ia7da132d5f49ea210295c18fb83cc807e6257f52
Closes-Bug: 1365699

commit_message:
all non debug log messages should be translated

Update a number of files to add missing translation support.
This patch adds a new hacking check - K005 - that ensures that
all log messages, except debug ones, have translations.

Change-Id: Idb86f7a74abbe0282c3d39521541e3e54618c094

commit_message:
Fixing subworkflow resolution algorithm

* Made necessary changes to be able to use short workflow names in DSL
  if they are defined within the same workbook as a calling workflow.
  The algorithm first tries to find a workflow assuming it's in the
  same workbook and if it doesn't exist then uses its name defined
  in DSL as a global name to find the workflow DB instance without
  prefixing it.

Change-Id: Id118cd89ebf290e49210a1699d422587b73c9d1f

commit_message:
Validation Input Objects

Specify schemas by an object. This means that we are going to pass an
object to controllers so that we can add methods and additional
validation logic (not controlled by jsonschema) to the input objects.

Change-Id: I2b104a4b7b758707b15eb74c736d12005ac1c5af

In the glance chapter of the installation guide, we configure
the notifier to use messaging. Glance notifications only appear
useful to environments using the glance ceilometer agent. Not
all environments use ceilometer and the associated queue could
become large without a consumer. We can remove the notifier keys
from the glance chapter since the glance ceilometer agent section

commit_message:
Remove optional notifier keys from glance

In the glance chapter of the installation guide, we configure
the notifier to use messaging. Glance notifications only appear
useful to environments using the glance ceilometer agent. Not
all environments use ceilometer and the associated queue could
become large without a consumer. We can remove the notifier keys
from the glance chapter since the glance ceilometer agent section
includes them.

I will fix this issue in the Juno version with a separate patch.

Change-Id: Id4e4dd97494dc84cf76203d54a92e035ffd997f6
Partial-Bug: #1360552

commit_message:
No default assignment backend

As a migation hack, Keystone assumed  that Assignments would be stored
in LDAP if A)  Identity was in LDAP and B) the Assignment driver was
not specified.  This is change removes that assumption.

People that are living with this assumption will now have to explicitly set
the Assignemtn driver to LDAP

Change-Id: I18c947df1fe927b3e23c3e535367a1aae2589d22

commit_message:
Remove optional notifier keys from glance

In the glance chapter of the installation guide, we configure
the notifier to use messaging. Glance notifications only appear
useful to environments using the glance ceilometer agent. Not
all environments use ceilometer and the associated queue could
become large without a consumer. We can remove the notifier keys
from the glance chapter since the glance ceilometer agent section
includes them.

Change-Id: I186cf4e54fa5e6c1389be2b5ea33d124abb483ff
Closes-Bug: #1360552

commit_message:
Add code/api documentation

Once we use the pbr based build to generate files, we prune
the indexes to remove references to code we would like to
hide like the common modules and private modules in conf.py.
We reuse the same excluded_patterns variable that is already
used in Sphinx and filter these modules from autoindex.rst

Closes-Bug: #1364140

Change-Id: Iebee287fe016f8a41a13e64b10f4ee02137043f8

commit_message:
Validates URL when creating/updating endpoints

This will help prevent invalid data from getting into the backend. The
existing validation was moved from the controller to the manager so that
the validation happens even when the manager is used directly.

Closes-Bug: #1230279
Change-Id: I4df4cadd03fbddd09bb07f42454d5c8eb6a396ab

I am not sure if we should merge odp file, can we discuss this over the review system or(and) IRC meeting?'}, {'account_id': 11889, 'date': '2014-09-08 16:09:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

This is a student template to present their plans to the rest of the class. 

We could ask them to do it with Landslide, but than again, almost all students already have experience with "classical" presentation software, so making these with Landslide adds (unneeded?) complexity to the process. They should be concentrating on content, not tools.'}, {'account_id': 11109, 'date': '2014-09-08 16:26:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I agree that ODP is better suited for the target audience, and I support the choice of format for that reason, even if it makes reviewing harder.

slide 3: s/chose/choose/

slide 4: s/messenging/messaging/

slide 5: s/english/English/

slide 6: s/messenging/messaging/

slide 8: s/Who will/To whom will/

slide 11: s/ Is cherry/Is cherry/'}, {'account_id': 11889, 'date': '2014-09-08 16:38:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I also forgot to add this earlier:

ODP is suited ONLY here, in this context, not in general. This template is also not going to change often, so difficult reviewing is not such a big deal.'}, {'account_id': 11889, 'date': '2014-09-08 17:47:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 6923, 'date': '2014-09-08 17:48:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
Adding a template for students to develop their final presentation

At the end of the class, each student will have to prepare a
presentation to illustrate what they're going to work on in the
future months and also excercise a little the skills learned.

This file is a template that can be distributed during classes.

Change-Id: I0d4971b1dfca7053c2c31cf275c93eadd4ed69f0

shorter uuid tokens

This produces shorter UUID tokens (21 OR 22 chars) by encoding the
random UUID using base 62.

commit_message:
Avoid testing code duplication which introduced testing bugs

SecurityGroupAgentEnhancedRpcTestCase duplicated code in
SecurityGroupAgentRpcTestCase setUp, also
TestSecurityGroupAgentEnhancedRpcWithIptables duplicated
code from TestSecurityGroupAgentWithIptables setUp()
introducing bugs by improper initialization, like a missing
    self.iptables.use_ipv6 = True
which in combination with tests.unit.test_ipv6.TestIsEnabled
produced inconsistent testing results.

Change-Id: Ic0b596b6fe1d8273df197e9426abad818832c00a
Closes-bug: #1365829

commit_message:
Use oslo.utils

Modules `strutils`, `timeutils` and `network_utils` from common code are
graduated in `oslo.utils`, so we can:
 1. remove `novaclient.openstack.common.network_utils` and use
    `oslo.utils.netutils` instead.
 2. use `oslo.utils.encodeutils` and `oslo.utils.strutils` instead of
    `novaclient.openstack.common.strutils`.
 3. use `oslo.utils.timeutils` instead of
    `novaclient.openstack.common.timeutils`.

Additional information:
 - modules `importutils`, `strutils` and `timeutils` from
   `novaclient.openstack.common` cannot be removed, because:
   - importutils is used by apiclient and jsonutils;
   - strutils is used by apiclient, cliutils and jsonutils;
   - timeutils is used by jsonutils
 - additional check for `safe_encode` in Py3 is required, since
   If91a866d864a22d28a352152beff4c7406a27b7b was merged.

Change-Id: Ib8d79d9c85af4916e87a76a1a67a13488ddaa111

commit_message:
Fixed heat-engine service stop.

* altered engine.pp for heat-engine service stopping during
update from 5.0 to 5.0.2
* altered pacemaker resource name from heat-engine to p_heat-engine
Closes-Bug: #1364026

Change-Id: Ic06bf843b22013d1eceb0f9881b1ee12681874b5

commit_message:
virt: canonicalize 'amd64' arch name into 'x86_64'

The Triple-O project uses an unusual name of 'amd64' for
the architecture name in Ironic compute nodes, instead of
the standardized 'x86_64'. Ensure the former is canonicalized
into the latter, so scheduler filters continue to match

Closes-bug: #1365750
Change-Id: Ib3200867763f0ecf158341f7dfdface82b309349

commit_message:
Reverse diff check in check_uptodate

Check_uptodate creates what it thinks our example conf should look like,
and compares that to what we actually have. In case of an error, it shows
a diff of the two files, but the diff is effectively how "expected" was
changed to produce "actual".

By reversing the comparison order, the diff is then the changes to apply to
"actual" to get "expected". We can apply that diff with patch to quickly
resolve the problems check_uptodate found.

Change-Id: I805c2097ef271b403add81702638b5c75df4c25e

commit_message:
Ignore 'dynamic' addr flag on bridge configuration

When setting the bridge up, if that flag is present but not
ignored, the delete command will fail and may leave the
interface and the bridge in an inconsistent state.

Closes-Bug: #1274611
Related-Bug: #1077066
Change-Id: Iff65d61d724d0de5d8173ac37f7f748aa23e5d8b
(cherry picked from commit 0d447f6edd406547e828c592823ac6624e56e91f)

commit_message:
Call policy.init() once per API request

This patch changes the policy engine behaviour and the API base
controller in order to ensure policy.init is invoked only once
for each API request.
This will avoid issues arising from policy file updates during
API processing and speed up response generation for list operations,
by about 5%.

This patch also removes an obsolete TODO comment.

Change-Id: I108ebd26fccdea19cb00959f70d87c3bc1587df9
Closes-Bug: 1302611
(cherry picked from commit 1d41ba485f060a4d6dbe0767845391f955247b08)

commit_message:
Keystone access log in key-access screen

When Keystone was run in Apache Httpd the access log wasn't in a
screen. A new screen called key-access is now started with
Keystone's access log.

Change-Id: Ie1f4d4b679e1b9c87f0cea37deb25f7b6636fe01
Closes-Bug: #1359995

subject: Change httpd Keystone access log to keystone_access.log

commit_message:
Change httpd Keystone access log to keystone_access.log

Keystone's access log was going to httpd/access.log, which is the
common place for all access logging. This made it difficult to see
Keystone accesses apart from other access. Keystone's access log
will now be keystone_access.log

This makes the Keystone configuration similar to Horizon which uses
horizon_access.log.

Change-Id: I6e5ac121302b3d138758e6c49dffa9f05ad2fb85
Partial-Bug: #1359995

commit_message:
Use 'replica' instead of 'slave'

Replace the mysql-specific term 'slave' with the more general term
'replica'.

In order to merge properly the client currently handles both 'slave' and
'replica' in certain cases. The 'slave' support will be removed completely
once the trove runtime is updated to be in sync.

Change-Id: Id22d18a84a4ac104ff8af09959e8eb2ae0102e97
Co-Authored-By: Nikhil Manchanda <SlickNik@gmail.com>

commit_message:
libvirt: do not fail instance destroy, if mount_device is missing

In some cases, a volume does not have a mount_device field populated
in the device_mapping, especially for LXC instances. LXC instances
does not have a disk_bus mapping in get_dev_prefix_for_disk_bus()
and that results in mount_device being set to None.

Related to blueprint libvirt-start-lxc-from-block-devices

Change-Id: Idbd4ced0337c64003af08ac0497008878fb1c2e1

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Gerrit_Workflow

commit_message:
Synchronize disable_dhcp_helper to avoid race condition

This patch uses the @utils.synchronized decorator to provide
a lock on the disable_dhcp_helper to prevent multiple accesses
to the function, as seen when calls to refresh_dhcp_helper
and disable_dhcp_helper occur consecutively. self.cache is not
thread-safe which leads to unpredictable behaviour if
disable_dhcp_helper is accessed multiple times simultaneously.

Change-Id: Idb0019ce806640bd6e6c7c028631e780e4b68a3b
Closes-Bug: 1233368
Closes-Bug: 1234026

commit_message:
Fix password reveal icon for Bootstrap 3

Bootstrap 3 uses different classes for icons, so a change in the
CSS and JavaScript is needed to keep the password reveal button
working.

Change-Id: If963b8b0805a6a0506bf3ef625c4271bf4d91067

commit_message:
Add a dox.yml config file

Dox is a new tool similar to tox but on docker. One of the benefits is
that it eliminates the need of installing all the package dependencies,
which removes the burden from developers.

The tool is still under heavy development but since Zaqar's test suite
is clean and organized, it may be a good project for early adoption.

Change-Id: Iec2698448618fee3019a6877c5c2ae87fda677b6

commit_message:
Add ZAQAR_TEST_EVERYTHING to enable all tests

We've a way to enable some tests that are environment dependant but
there's no good way, other than setting all those variables, to enable
all tests in a specific environment.

This patch adds a new variable to do the above. It also DRYes a bit the
check of env variables that have been set.

Change-Id: Ia75925b4e22e27dab4d67caf67db80c191717caf

[{'created': '2014-08-27 14:13:23.000000000', 'message': "Fix master status validation while replica provisioning

Use case: Master instance is not ACTIVE.
In this case we need to check if master is
ACTIVE and raise HTTP 422 UnprocessableEntity in cases when status
is something else than ACTIVE (BUILD, ERROR, BACKUP, FAILED, RESIZE, etc.).

Reasons:
 - Slave can be created from master that's not in ACTIVE state.

Changes:
 - adding master status validation step;
 - refactoring validate_can_perform_action method of instance/models.py
   to extract common logic for generic method that validates status of instance.

commit_message:
Fix master status validation while replica provisioning

Use case: Master instance is not ACTIVE.
In this case we need to check if master is
ACTIVE and raise HTTP 422 UnprocessableEntity in cases when status
is something else than ACTIVE (BUILD, ERROR, BACKUP, FAILED, RESIZE, etc.).

Reasons:
 - Slave can be created from master that's not in ACTIVE state.

Changes:
 - adding master status validation step;
 - refactoring validate_can_perform_action method of instance/models.py
   to extract common logic for generic method that validates status of instance.

Change-Id: I5bb8cabc8db3b5ff1159dd3e29953435d99b5dce
Closes-Bug: #1357705

commit_message:
Update overcloud examples for ExtraConfig

The existing examples for the overcloud ExtraConfig options
use an ironic setting that would likely never apply (Ironic
isn't for the overcloud).

This patch modifies the default section setting to use
the Nova force_config_drive option instead as a
config example.

Change-Id: Ieb893552fe9466b90b9d9a831a676d114efb6db1
